    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.6.14" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline><hi rend="underline">7 August 1919</hi></dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear John Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>               
                <p>So good a letter as John's deserves lots better of an answer than this hasty note, but if I wait longer for a chance to write it, procrastination may swallow it whole. So here's just to say <hi rend="underline">Thank you</hi> for your fine + stimulating response to my letter regarding <unclear>Richarts +  Dirst</unclear> that I might <unclear/> <unclear>beg for</unclear> and there in your great silences, then from sun up till <unclear>sundown +</unclear> again till sun-up; for this letter-writing (I agree with you) is as good as a <unclear/> for the <unclear/>intimate<unclear> wonder of peace</unclear>.</p>
                
                <p>God speed you in your work of great horizons!</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute><unclear/></salute>
                    <signed>--Percy Mackaye--</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope"> <!--envelope included w/ 8-9-19 letter from J.G. Howard but almost certainly belongs w/ j4a.6.14-->
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.6.15-20_0005"/> 
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <unclear/> Percy Mackaye
                    <unclear/>, New York
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    WYOMING AUG 7 5PM 1919 N.Y.
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>2 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POSTAGE 2 CEN<unclear cert="high">TS</unclear> 2</p>
                </figure>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John Neihardt Esq.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Nebraska</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <note type="recipient">Percy Mackaye
                    (poet)</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
